it advised that the respondent was prepared to accept liability for the applicant's claim and to pay compensation for the period from april 1976 to february 1979.
on 19 march 2004 the tribunal determined that the applicant was entitled to compensation for schizophrenia and alcoholism pursuant to s 124 of the safety, rehabilitation and compensation act 1988 (cth); the incapacity was partial in that the applicant suffered an 80 per cent loss of capacity to work; and the compensation related to the period from 3 april 1976 to 2 april 1978.